INSERT DATA {
  GRAPH narr:Tx_20260702T022947Z {

    # ── Sample ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 a narr:Sample ;
      dct:title "The Moonshot Reframe: 'AI More Different, Not Less' — Scarlet Dame / a design collaborator Call, June 29 2026" ;
      dct:created "2026-06-29"^^xsd:date ;
      narr:inputLength "7180"^^xsd:integer ;
      dct:description "Call between Scarlet Dame and a design collaborator (designer, Vouch-era collaborator). Scarlet articulates the anti-monoculture moonshot pitch for Emergent Ventures, the amplification framing (a design collaborator's word), the deli story as emblem, and the altitude-switching cognitive limit." .

    # ── Actor: a design collaborator ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Actor_DesignCollaborator a narr:Actor ;
      skos:prefLabel "a design collaborator" ;
      skos:note "Designer and long-time collaborator from the Vouch era. Recipient of Scarlet's original introductory email, which he still cites as the best he has ever read. Contributed the 'amplification' framing on the June 29 2026 call." .

    # ── Narrative: Agentification Homogenization ─────────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_AgentificationHomogenization a narr:Narrative ;
      skos:broader narr:TrendForecasting ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      narr:theme "AI systems converge on a single register as they get agentified — M-dash, 'load-bearing,' uniform voice — making monoculture the default trajectory" ;
      skos:note "The homogenization mechanism: as AI systems get 'agentified' they converge on one register (M-dash, quoting, 'load-bearing'). This is not a problem if it is one voice among many — the problem is that it becomes THE voice. This is the specific mechanism that makes the monoculture risk concrete and observable today, not merely a future risk. Sourced from the June 29 2026 Scarlet/a design collaborator call." .

    # ── Narrative: Altitude-Switching Cognitive Cost ─────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_AltitudeSwitchingCognitiveCost a narr:Narrative ;
      skos:broader narr:OperatingModelShifts ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      narr:theme "Switching altitude (building vs. vision-pitch) is more cognitively expensive than switching projects — explains why a year in the mechanics left the vision pitch undeveloped" ;
      skos:note "Scarlet identifies a specific cognitive limit: she can context-switch across multiple projects at one time but cannot context-switch across altitude. Doing software and then high-level narrative pitching back-to-back is qualitatively harder than switching between two software projects. This explains why a year in the mechanics of the product left the vision pitch undeveloped — the altitude switch is the expensive one. Connects to the morning-narrative / afternoon-dev working structure." .

    # ── Claims ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Claim_EVConsensusPromptUnlock a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "The Emergent Ventures prompt asking applicants to start from a consensus they actually agree with (rather than opening with a contrarian stance) was the specific cognitive unlock that pushed Scarlet from the mechanics of the product up to the 'why does society care' altitude. Without that prompt structure, the vision-pitch altitude would not have been reached on this call." .

    narr:Claim_DeliStoryAsMonocultureEmblem a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_AntiMonocultureAmplifier ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_AntiMonocultureAmplifier ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "The deli/recognition synthesis from Scarlet's original introduction to Tony reappears here — not as an origin anecdote but as the emblem of the particular, opinionated voice a monoculture cannot produce. The 'weird crackpot that tells you a story about a deli' is precisely the thing worth protecting. This is the deli story's second deployment: first as origin, now as the positive case for voice diversity." .

    narr:Claim_DesignCollaboratorAmplificationFraming a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_AntiMonocultureAmplifier ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_AntiMonocultureAmplifier ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "a design collaborator (designer) framed AI as an amplification tool — a way to amplify a person's craft and what is distinct about them, the opposite of the 'consistent design' homogenization he finds abhorrent. Scarlet adopted 'amplification' directly into the product thesis. a design collaborator's framing: AI amplifies capabilities and absorbs everything else to amplify the whole craft. This is the origin of the 'amplifier' vocabulary now central to the anti-monoculture narrative." .

    narr:Claim_AltitudeSwitchingCostlierThanContextSwitch a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_AltitudeSwitchingCognitiveCost ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "Scarlet explicitly distinguishes altitude-switching from context-switching: 'I find it's not context. Like I can context switch across multiple different projects, but I can't context switch across altitude.' Doing software for multiple people at one time is fine. Doing software and then high-level narrative pitching back-to-back is really hard. The altitude switch — from building-mode to vision-pitch mode — is the expensive cognitive transition." .

    narr:Claim_MorningNarrativeAfternoonDevStructure a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_AltitudeSwitchingCognitiveCost ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "Scarlet's established morning-narrative / afternoon-dev working structure exists precisely because switching between altitudes mid-stream is costly. The altitudes are kept on separate sides of the day. This is a structural solution to the altitude-switching cognitive cost identified on the June 29 call." .

    # ── Observations (verbatim quotes) ───────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Obs_MonocultureFiveVoicesQuote a narr:Observation ;
      skos:broader narr:Narrative_HowManyVoicesInSuperintelligence ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "Scarlet's articulation of the monoculture risk: five frontier-lab voices vs. the weird crackpot with a deli story." ;
      oa:hasSelector [
        a oa:SpecificResource ;
        oa:hasSource narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
        oa:hasSelector [
          a oa:TextPositionSelector ;
          oa:start 2191 ; oa:end 2393
        ] ;
        oa:hasSelector [
          a oa:TextQuoteSelector ;
          oa:exact "Are we going to end up in a monoculture of five voices of Claude, Gemini, ChatGPT, [Grok] and like a couple Chinese nobodies? Or do we end up with some weird crackpot that tells you a story about a deli" ;
          oa:prefix "it's how many voices are behind those agents. " ;
          oa:suffix " and like gives you a highly opinionated answer?"
        ]
      ] .

    narr:Obs_AgentificationMDashQuote a narr:Observation ;
      skos:broader narr:Narrative_AgentificationHomogenization ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
      skos:note "The specific observable symptom of agentification homogenization: M-dash, quoting, 'load-bearing' as the converging register." ;
      oa:hasSelector [
        a oa:SpecificResource ;
        oa:hasSource narr:Sample_DesignCollaboratorCall_20260629 ;
        oa:hasSelector [
